{
  "doc_id": "28718",
  "text": "Polyvinylidene fluoride (PVDF) as a semi-crystalline polymer exhibits high mechanical strength, thermal stability, and excellent aging resistance [CITATION_1] , which are important for the application of the TOEC process. Graphene is a monolayer of carbon atoms, which has been successfully used as an additive in polymers in order to reinforce the thermal conductivity and mechanical strength. The incorporation of graphene can also enhance the hydrophobicity of the polymer due to its intrinsic hydrophobic nature [CITATION_2] . Therefore, the PVDF/graphene membrane can be a candidate for the application in the TOEC process. In order to obtain the optimized membrane for the TOEC process, it is necessary to know the temperature dependence of the pore structures of the membrane.",
